TITLE: Using puppeteer-extra-plugin-repl in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of how to use the puppeteer-extra-plugin-repl with puppeteer-extra. It demonstrates launching a browser, navigating to a page, and starting interactive REPL sessions for both page and browser instances.
SOURCE: https://github.com/berstend/puppeteer-extra/blob/master/packages/puppeteer-extra-plugin-repl/readme.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const puppeteer = require('puppeteer-extra')
puppeteer.use(require('puppeteer-extra-plugin-repl')())

puppeteer.launch({ headless: true }).then(async browser => {
  const page = await browser.newPage()
  await page.goto('https://example.com')

  // Start an interactive REPL here with the `page` instance.
  await page.repl()
  // Afterwards start REPL with the `browser` instance.
  await browser.repl()

  await browser.close()
})
```

